<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="140" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,358,565]" pageId="8" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,431,457]" pageId="8" pageNumber="140">Remarks.</emphasis>
Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[471,553,430,457]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–27" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,589,1698]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[177,1411,586,1707]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25–27. Male of Geodromicus frigidus (North Korea): 25–habitus, 26–aedeagus, parameral view, 27–aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bar: 2.00 mm (Fig. 25), 0.2 mm (Figs. 26–27)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884806" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884806/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="140">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
. Aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation box="[735,870,431,457]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–27" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,589,1698]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[177,1411,586,1707]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25–27. Male of Geodromicus frigidus (North Korea): 25–habitus, 26–aedeagus, parameral view, 27–aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bar: 2.00 mm (Fig. 25), 0.2 mm (Figs. 26–27)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884806" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884806/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="140">Figs. 26–27</figureCitation>
. The species was known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1208,1317,431,457]" name="Mongolia" pageId="8" pageNumber="140">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1369,1436,431,457]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="140">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Smetana, A." box="[159,323,467,493]" pageId="8" pageNumber="140" pagination="226 - 238" refId="ref19808" refString="Smetana, A. (1968) Ergebnisse der zoologischen Forschungen von Dr. Z. Kaszab in der Mongolei. 127. Staphylinidae III. Unterfamilien Oxytelinae und Oxyporinae (Coleoptera). Acta entomologica Bohemoslovaca, 65 (3), 226 - 238." type="journal article" year="1968">Smetana 1968</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Shavrin, A. V." box="[335,491,467,493]" pageId="8" pageNumber="140" pagination="151 - 190" refId="ref19571" refString="Shavrin, A. V. (2018) The lestevoides species group of the genus Geodromicus Redtenbacher, 1857 (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Omaliinae). Zootaxa, 4378 (2), 151 - 190. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4378.2.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Shavrin 2018</bibRefCitation>
). The shape of the apical portion of the aedeagus of the specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[1295,1436,467,493]" name="North Korea" pageId="8" pageNumber="140">North Korea</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[160,240,503,530]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–27" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,589,1698]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[177,1411,586,1707]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25–27. Male of Geodromicus frigidus (North Korea): 25–habitus, 26–aedeagus, parameral view, 27–aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bar: 2.00 mm (Fig. 25), 0.2 mm (Figs. 26–27)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884806" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884806/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="140">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) is identical to those specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[658,767,503,529]" name="Mongolia" pageId="8" pageNumber="140">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[820,887,503,529]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="140">China</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[901,1034,503,529]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–34" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1649,1674]" captionTargetBox="[162,1418,204,1620]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1435,181,1624]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 30–34. Male of Geodromicus hammondi (Anhui): 30–abdominal tergite VIII, 31–abdominal sternite VIII, 32–aedeagus, dorsal view, 33–aedeagus, lateral view, 34–aedeagus, parameral view. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884810" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884810/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="140">
Figs. 
<quantity box="[964,1034,503,529]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.128" metricValueMax="8.636" metricValueMin="7.62" pageId="8" pageNumber="140" unit="in" value="32.0" valueMax="34.0" valueMin="30.0">30–34</quantity>
</figureCitation>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Shavrin, A. V." box="[1068,1249,503,529]" pageId="8" pageNumber="140" pagination="151 - 190" refId="ref19571" refString="Shavrin, A. V. (2018) The lestevoides species group of the genus Geodromicus Redtenbacher, 1857 (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Omaliinae). Zootaxa, 4378 (2), 151 - 190. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4378.2.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Shavrin (2018))</bibRefCitation>
. The distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shavrin" authorityYear="2018" box="[182,303,539,565]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geodromicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frigidus">
<emphasis box="[182,303,539,565]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="140">G. frigidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[339,406,539,565]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="140">China</collectingCountry>
is shown in 
<figureCitation box="[547,642,539,565]" captionStart="FIGURE 113" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,1064,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[180,1408,1064,1892]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 113. Distribution of 21 species of Geodromicus in China: 1–G. abdominalis, 2–G. amplissimus, 3–G. aokii, 4–G. beibienkoi, 5–G. chinensis, 6–G. cupreostigma, 7–G. formosanus, 8–G. frigidus, 9–G. hammondi, 10–G. lestevoides, 11–G. magnus sp. n., 12–G. namucuoicus sp. n., 13–G. ohkurai, 14–G. philydroides, 15–G. shii sp. n., 16–G. sibiricus, 17–G. sinuatocollis, 18–G. sinuatus, 19–G. smetanai, 20–G. subquadratus sp. n., 21–G. taiwanensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884852" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884852/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="140">Fig. 113</figureCitation>
. The species is here recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1039,1179,539,565]" name="North Korea" pageId="8" pageNumber="140">North Korea</collectingCountry>
for the first time.
</paragraph>
